aria-labelledby=\"pdfDropdown\" class=\"dropdown-menu dropdown-menu-right\"><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub\">Add selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html?finish_action=mydocs_topic_and_sub_head\">Add Topic &amp; Subtopics with topic head</a><a class=\"zDocsAddTopicButton zDocsMyDocsMenuItem dropdown-item\" href=\"/de-DE/auth/login?redirect=/bundle/uniface_104/page/ulo1665702550460.html?finish_action=mydocs_pub\">Add entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsWatchButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Watch\" class=\"d-lg-flex d-none zDocsSubscribeButton\" data-tooltip-content=\"Watch\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsSubscribeButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-eye zDocsSubscribeButton\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-eye\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsSubscribeButton\">Watch</span></span></div><div class=\"zDocsExportPdfMenu zDocsExportMenu\" data-testid=\"export-pdf-menu\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Download PDF\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Download PDF\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#ZdExportPDFModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3616336\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_3616336\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 09, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104ulo1665702550460.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ulo1665702550460.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/ulo1665702550460.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"ulo1665702550460\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__development_object_308886\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">A Uniface Development Object is an abstract data type that defines the characteristics and behavior of a logical application unit, such as a Component, Field, Message, Library, and so on.\n </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__p_d94469e1_d94470e1_d94471e1\">During the build process, development objects may be compiled into executable <dfn class=\"term\">runtime objects</dfn> or used to generate other runtime objects that can be used in the deployed application or during development.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__p_d94472e1_d94473e1_d94474e1\">There are many types (or <dfn class=\"term\">specializations</dfn>) of Development Object. Some describe application components (such as <dfn class=\"term\">Dynamic Server Page</dfn> and <dfn class=\"term\">Service</dfn>), others describe the application data (such as <dfn class=\"term\">Modeled Entity</dfn> and <dfn class=\"term\">Modeled Field</dfn>), and yet others can be shared across the application (such as <dfn class=\"term\">Message</dfn> and <dfn class=\"term\">Global ProcScript</dfn>).</p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__topic_d62902e1_d62903e1_d62904e1_d62905e1_d62906e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d98836e83\"> Characteristics </h2>\n<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__table_d10439e1_d10440e1_d10441e1\"><caption></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Object type code: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> — </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Main Development Object? </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">No</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Part of: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">Development Object</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Contains: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Development Object, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jgi1665702550212.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jgi1665702550212.html\" title=\"A Property is a named, typed attribute of Development Object that defines a characteristic or behavior of the object. Each property has a descriptive name, a literal name, a data type, and a value. If no value is specified, a default value may be used.\">Property</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cny1665702550298.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cny1665702550298.html\" title=\"A Code Container is a type of Property that holds code, such as ProcScript, JavaScript, or HTML. It can contain one or more code modules, such as triggers, operations, functions, or entries, or HTML for the layout.\">Code Container</a>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Generalization: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> — </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Specializations: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"srw1665702550375.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/srw1665702550375.html\" title=\"A Main Development Object is a Development Object that has no parent object, is maintained using a dedicated editor, and can be saved and exported as a single unit, with all its children.\">Main Development Object</a> and subobjects of main development\n                        objects: <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36677e1_d36678e1_d36679e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yth1665702550544.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yth1665702550544.html\" title=\"A Component Entity is a Development Object that represents data that is owned by a Component. It is part of the Component’s structure and is maintained as part of the Component, although it may reference and inherit from a Modeled Entity.\">Component Entity</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36680e1_d36681e1_d36682e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zyj1665702550619.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zyj1665702550619.html\" title=\"A Component Field is a Development Object that represents a unit of data in a Component Entity.\">Component Field</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36683e1_d36684e1_d36685e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"sfg1665702550701.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/sfg1665702550701.html\" title=\"A Device Translation Table is a Development Object that maps Uniface output to device-specific output formats for printers and character-based (CHUI) screens. It makes it possible for Uniface to support a wide variety of hardware platforms, including their output devices.\">Device Translation Table</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36686e1_d36687e1_d36688e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wmu1665702708557.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wmu1665702708557.html\" title=\"A Drag-and-Drop Format is Development Object that defines a default action, pop-up menu, and icon that can be used when performing drag-and-drop actions in the tree and picture widgets of forms. It is not used for drag-and-drop widgets.\">Drag-and-Drop Format</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36689e1_d36690e1_d36691e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"gya1665702610097.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/gya1665702610097.html\" title=\"A Frame is a Development Object that graphically represents a Development Object in the layout of a Form or Report component.\">Frame</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36692e1_d36693e1_d36694e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"amz1665702708928.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/amz1665702708928.html\" title=\"A Global ProcScript is a Development Object that defines a ProcScript function that is linked into components at runtime when called by ProcScript in the component.\">Global ProcScript</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36695e1_d36696e1_d36697e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"luz1665702709079.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/luz1665702709079.html\" title=\"A Global Variable is a Development Object that defines a typed variable that can be accessed by all ProcScript in the application.\">Global Variable</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36698e1_d36699e1_d36700e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fbw1665702713269.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fbw1665702713269.html\" title=\"An IncludeScript is a Development Object that defines a fragment of script that can be inserted into ProcScript using the #include directive.\">IncludeScript</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36701e1_d36702e1_d36703e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vuv1665702701508.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vuv1665702701508.html\" title=\"A Key is a Development Object that designates a field or combination of fields as a Primary Key, Candidate Key, or Index.\">Key</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36704e1_d36705e1_d36706e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"zxb1665702710155.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/zxb1665702710155.html\" title=\"A Keyboard Translation Table is a Development Object that maps user input to structure editor functions recognized by Uniface.\">Keyboard Translation Table</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36707e1_d36708e1_d36709e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"wyt1665702609153.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/wyt1665702609153.html\" title=\"A Label is a Development Object that contains text that appears on a presentation component. Labels have properties, but most cannot be set dynamically.\">Label</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36710e1_d36711e1_d36712e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"vqz1665702709424.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/vqz1665702709424.html\" title=\"A Menu is a Development Object that defines a Uniface menu bar, dropdown menu, or pop-up menu for a desktop application. It is cannot be used in web applications.\">Menu</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36713e1_d36714e1_d36715e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"pdp1665702709496.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/pdp1665702709496.html\" title=\"A Message is a Development Object that defines text to be used in the application, such as a label, help text, prompt, or error message.\">Message</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36716e1_d36717e1_d36718e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"hzd1665702710226.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hzd1665702710226.html\" title=\"A Modeled Entity Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for the Database Interface property of a Database Entity.\">Modeled Entity Interface</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36719e1_d36720e1_d36721e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"yzg1665702711012.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/yzg1665702711012.html\" title=\"A Modeled Field Interface is a Development Object that defines a reusable value for the Database Interface property of a Database Field.\">Modeled Field Interface</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36722e1_d36723e1_d36724e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ijx1665702711766.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ijx1665702711766.html\" title=\"A Modeled Field Layout is a Development Object that defines the way data is displayed.\">Modeled Field Layout</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36725e1_d36726e1_d36727e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"bbr1665702712405.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bbr1665702712405.html\" title=\"A Modeled Field Syntax is a Development Object that defines some validation rules for data entry in the Field, such as the allowed characters, and field display and control attributes, such dimming and auto-jump.\">Modeled Field Syntax</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36728e1_d36729e1_d36730e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nqg1665702709724.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nqg1665702709724.html\" title=\"A Panel is a Development Object that defines a toolbar containing buttons to execute structure editor functions and operations on the active form.\">Panel</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36731e1_d36732e1_d36733e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fct1665702713420.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fct1665702713420.html\" title=\"A Reference Development Object holds the URL of another development object and enables its parent object to access the information in the referenced object. It can be created, modified, and deleted without affecting the object that it references.\">Reference Development Object</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36734e1_d36735e1_d36736e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"xtb1665702702029.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xtb1665702702029.html\" title=\"A Relationship is a Development Object that represents an association between one entity and another. It specifies the primary or candidate keys to be used in maintaining the association, as well as the delete constraints to be used when deleting occurrences in the related entities.\">Relationship</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36737e1_d36738e1_d36739e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"qnm1665702714020.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/qnm1665702714020.html\" title=\"A Signature Implementation is a Development Object that defines the technology used to implement a signature, such as Uniface, COM, SOAP and so on. A Signature can have multiple implementations. Each Signature Implementation captures the technology-specific properties of the Signature, Signature Operation, and Signature Parameters.\">Signature Implementation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36740e1_d36741e1_d36742e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"dlk1665702714091.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/dlk1665702714091.html\" title=\"A Signature Operation is a Development Object that describes the public method of a signature.\">Signature Operation</a>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36743e1_d36744e1_d36745e1\">\n<a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"jha1665702714162.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/jha1665702714162.html\" title=\"A Signature Parameter is a Development Object that describes an argument that can be passed in or out of an operation.\">Signature Parameter</a>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Compilation output: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> Depends on the type of object </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> URI format: </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\"> — </td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__p_d94478e1_d94479e1_d94480e1\">Development Object is an abstract, complex data type\n            that has the following characteristics:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36746e1_d36747e1_d36748e1\">It can have a parent development object </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36749e1_d36750e1_d36751e1\">It can have can have three types of children: <ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36752e1_d36753e1_d36754e1\">\n<dfn class=\"term\">Properties</dfn>, including Name, Description and Comment, and other\n                     properties that are specific to its type </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36755e1_d36756e1_d36757e1\">\n<dfn class=\"term\">Code containers</dfn>, which are type-specific properties that hold\n                     ProcScript, JavaScript, or HTML </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36758e1_d36759e1_d36760e1\">Other development objects </li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__li_d36761e1_d36762e1_d36763e1\">It has a case-insensitive name that is unique for\n               its type. <p class=\"p\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__p_d94481e1_d94482e1_d94483e1\">Each object is uniquely identified by\n                  its type, parent names, and name. Objects of a different type can have the same\n                  name.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__p_d94484e1_d94485e1_d94486e1\">For example, a message and a component can both\n                  have the name <code class=\"ph codeph\">AABBCC</code>, but they are different types of objects, so\n                  the identifier is unique (<code class=\"ph codeph\">msg:AABBCC</code> vs\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">cpt:AABBCC</code>).</p>\n<div class=\"note important note_important\" id=\"ulo1665702550460__note_w1336ab1b5b7b7b5b5_w1337ab1b5b7b7b5_w1338ab1b5b7b7_w1339ab1b5b7_w1340ab1b5_w1341ab1\"><span class=\"note__title\">Important:</span> All types of component have the same type (<code class=\"ph codeph\">cpt</code>),\n                  so a Dynamic Server Page cannot have the same name as a Service.</div>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616336\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_3616336\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Development Object Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 09, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 A Uniface Development Object is an abstract data type that defines the characteristics and behavior of a logical application unit, such as a Component, Field, Message, Library, and so on. During the build process, development objects may be compiled into executable runtime objects or used to generate other runtime objects that can be used in the deployed application or during development. There are many types (or specializations ) of Development Object. Some describe application components (such as Dynamic Server Page and Service ), others describe the application data (such as Modeled Entity and Modeled Field ), and yet others can be shared across the application (such as Message and Global ProcScript ). Characteristics Object type code: — Main Development Object? No Part of: Development Object Contains: Development Object, Property , Code Container Generalization: — Specializations: Main Development Object and subobjects of main development objects: Component Entity Component Field Device Translation Table Drag-and-Drop Format Frame Global ProcScript Global Variable IncludeScript Key Keyboard Translation Table Label Menu Message Modeled Entity Interface Modeled Field Interface Modeled Field Layout Modeled Field Syntax Panel Reference Development Object Relationship Signature Implementation Signature Operation Signature Parameter Compilation output: Depends on the type of object URI format: — Development Object is an abstract, complex data type that has the following characteristics: It can have a parent development object It can have can have three types of children: Properties , including Name, Description and Comment, and other properties that are specific to its type Code containers , which are type-specific properties that hold ProcScript, JavaScript, or HTML Other development objects It has a case-insensitive name that is unique for its type. Each object is uniquely identified by its type, parent names, and name. Objects of a different type can have the same name. For example, a message and a component can both have the name AABBCC , but they are different types of objects, so the identifier is unique ( msg:AABBCC vs cpt:AABBCC ). Important: All types of component have the same type ( cpt ), so a Dynamic Server Page cannot have the same name as a Service. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}